'''Manuscript notes in ''Dictionary in Englysshe and Welshe''''' refers to a page of [[Index:Unpublished material|unpublished notes]] by [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] inserted in his copy of ''[[List of books in Tolkien's library#Dictionary in Englysshe and Welshe|Dictionary in Englysshe and Welshe]]''. The manuscript consists of a translation of the opening of the [[Welsh]] prologue.<ref name=TW>[[Carl Phelpstead]], ''[[Tolkien and Wales]]'', "Encountering Welsh", "Tolkien's Celtic Library", pp. 9-12</ref><ref name=Add>{{webcite|author=[[Christina Scull]], [[Wayne G. Hammond]]|articleurl=http://www.hammondandscull.com/addenda/chronology.html|articlename=Addenda and Corrigenda to ''The J.R.R. Tolkien Companion and Guide'' (2006) Vol. 1: Chronology|dated=|website=HS|accessed=31 July 2012}}</ref>

